Daimler, Nissan Expand Product Cooperation, Automobilwoche Says

-- B y   J u l i e   C r u z
-- 
2011-03-05T13:02:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-05/daimler-nissan-expand-product-cooperation-automobilwoche-says.html
  Daimler AG (DAI)  and Nissan Motor Co. are
cooperating to develop components that will be used in vehicles
from both manufacturers,  Automobilwoche  reported, citing
unidentified people with knowledge of the agreement.  The components would be used both for smaller Mercedes
models and for vehicles of Nissan’s Infiniti luxury brand, the
magazine said. Daimler is interested in Nissan’s expertise in
battery and hybrid technologies, Automobilwoche said, citing the
people.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Julie Cruz in Frankfurt at 
 jcruz6@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Rummer at   arummer@bloomberg.net  